The paper describes a program for reasoning in extensions of logical theories, which is a topic that falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the program uses specialized provers and SMT solvers, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). The program also has applications in software engineering (cs.SE) and formal languages (cs.FL) due to its ability to test satisfiability and generate models.
